    "biography": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Hild</strong> is a Dwarf innkeeper who runs the Broken Stair Inn â€” the only inn in Stairwatch. She asks no questions, charges fair prices, and waters the ale 'just enough to be annoying.' She knows Lew well â€” he owes her three nights' lodging.</p><p>Hild is practical, no-nonsense, and generous when earned. She is the warm heart of Stairwatch: practical kindness in a world that's running out of it.</p>",
      "director": "<p>Hild appears in <strong>Beat 5</strong> when the PCs arrive at Stairwatch, and again during the stay before departure.</p><p><strong>Key interactions:</strong></p><ul><li>Directs PCs to Lew: \"The Finder? Upstairs room, when he bothers to sleep here. More likely at the chandler's. He owes me three nights' lodging.\"</li><li>If PCs helped with the mine task: packs extra rations on the house. \"Bring that one-eyed bastard back alive. He owes me.\"</li><li><strong>Grafvitnir Pressure Check:</strong> A stranger at the Bone Market asks about the PCs. She says nothing, but warns the PCs afterward.</li></ul>",
